parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to loss of motive power, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle vibrates or shudders when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to loss of motive power, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the "Service Transmission" warning message is displayed
the transmission overheats
the vehicle vibrates or shudders when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to loss of motive power, accidents, or stranding the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Pump Belt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump belt can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of motive power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the oil warning light illuminates
the vehicle makes a loud noise or smoke comes from the engine
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shudders
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle makes a loud noise or smoke comes from the engine
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the purge canister valve system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle makes a loud noise or smoke comes from the engine
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the canister purge valve can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause fuel tank deformation and low fuel pressure.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
especially when refueling
the engine light comes on with code P1450
the vehicle shakes or shutters when starting
the fuel tank is deformed
low fuel pressure
and the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank deformation can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause low fuel pressure and difficulty starting the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
especially when refueling
the fuel tank is deformed
low fuel pressure
and the vehicle has difficulty starting.
